property_details: The Rosewood story began in 1979 with the renovation of a historic mansion in Dallas, Texas. The Mansion on Turtle Creek remains an icon in the world of hospitality to this day and a blueprint for all subsequent Rosewood endeavors. The ambition was to create a distinctive, luxurious, residential-style collection of properties, each to deliver a unique ambience and style defined by a gracious and passionate attention to detail. Unique to the Rosewood experience is a curated Sense of Place® conveyed through memorable personal journeys that are subtle, nonconventional, yet exquisite and relevant to the Gulf Coast culture. Even before the first sketches, long before interior design, we begin with understanding how the locale will inform our path. Throughout this evolution that ultimately leads to a highly serviced lifestyle, our intentions are to curate original moments, culturally relevant, but explored with fresh eyes. Our view is that this approach offers an experience and lifestyle where every day can be extraordinary. Genuine, personal and committed characterize Rosewood residential services. Our diverse, sophisticated, and knowledgeable staff caters to all lifestyles, ensuring an effortless and highly personalized homeownership experience. Our team sets out to understand the needs of our owners, tailoring services and anticipating needs, allowing us the ability to get to know them, and create unforgettable moments that will consistently surpass every expectation.
amenity_details: The residences sit atop an amenity level conceived, curated, appointed and graciously serviced by Rosewood. All the essentials are here, resort-like, beach-friendly amenities and services, fashioned to offer an intimate, private club atmosphere surrounded only by family and friends. The spaces are art-filled, the experience nuanced – a collection of moments for gathering or quiet escape, that are purposeful, considered and confidently executed. A result considerably greater than a sum of the parts. The entire club level, from fitness center to lounges and bistro and game rooms open seamlessly to a collection of social, as well as private gathering spaces. Just off the bar and restaurant is a zero-edge swimming pool and spa with sun shelf, day cabanas lounges. Both the pool and the spa/fitness areas share intimae seating groups, and a bocce court. The north-side gameroom and lounge open to the pet park, the chef’s gardens and a comfortable fire pit terrace, all inviting places for gathering with family and neighbors. On the beach, fronting the entire length of the residences is a lushly landscaped beach amenity, including a zero-edge swimming pool with sun shelves, day cabanas & lounge seating. There is a stylish pool pavilion with food and beverage service and two fire pits, and of course, plenty of room for paddleboard and beach toy storage. Social lounge with public & semi-private seating areas, Bistro Café with open kitchen, full bar, full dining service, separate main dining area accessible to pool deck, Owner’s private wine storage/locker, Fitness & locker rooms with massage, hot & cold salt pools & steam room, Game room with snacks, billiards, table tennis, jukebox, air hockey, arcade games, infant play area, 12-seat theater, Boardroom, Six Rosewood guest suites
developer_details: Along the storied Gulf Coast, from tony Naples to trending Sarasota, are landmarks of grace and sophistication. Condominiums yes, but beyond this they are monuments to quality and, commitment. All are exclusively residential, and as such are required to satisfy owners — a far more demanding audience than the transient hotel guest. For more than 50 years The Ronto Group has earned an enviable reputation for projects that make an immediate, and lasting contribution to their communities. The benefit to the future owners at Lido Key is a richly experienced developer, one that is passionate about quality, and as true to their word as their craft.
architect_details: Swedroe Architecture has been recognized as one of the Top Miami Architecture firms for over 45 years. The firm has designed and completed hundreds of architecture projects in Miami and around the world. From luxury high-rise condominiums, to elegant hotel-condominiums, each building is designed from the inside out to maximize overall building efficiency and utilization of space. As a result, its open, well-appointed, view-oriented, spectacular designs have consistently created enhanced value for both the property developer and the owners.
